title: Foodcycle
description: UK-wide community and volunteer run project that use end-of-day produce from supermarkets and local food suppliers, and turns them into nutritious food for the community, especially those on a low income, homeless, or vulnerable. Meals are vegetarian/vegan and free, though anybody can come along and leave a donation towards the meal. Served on Friday 7pm.
streetAddress: Friends Meeting House, Upper Goat Lane
